---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { translations, type Lang } from "../../../i18n/translations";
import CodeBlock from "../../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
import DocSidebar from "../../../components/docs/DocSidebar.astro";
import DocTOC from "../../../components/docs/DocTOC.astro";
import DocPagination from "../../../components/docs/DocPagination.astro";
import DocBreadcrumb from "../../../components/docs/DocBreadcrumb.astro";
import DocSearch from "../../../components/docs/DocSearch.astro";

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  return [
    { params: { lang: "en" } },
    { params: { lang: "it" } },
    { params: { lang: "id" } },
    { params: { lang: "ru" } },
    { params: { lang: "zh" } },
    { params: { lang: "ja" } },
  ];
}

const { lang } = Astro.params as { lang: Lang };
const t = translations[lang];
const d = t.docs.reporting;
const headings = [
  { id: "manual-collection", text: d.h_manualCollection, level: 2 },
  { id: "output-formats", text: d.h_outputFormats, level: 2 }
];

// page data

// page data
---

<Layout lang={lang} t={t}>
  <DocSidebar lang={lang} currentPath={Astro.url.pathname} headings={headings} />
  <div class="max-w-none lg:ml-96 px-6 lg:px-10 pt-24 lg:pt-28 pb-16 lg:pb-24">
    <div class="lg:flex lg:gap-0">
      <main class="flex-1 min-w-0 lg:pl-20 xl:pl-28">
        <DocBreadcrumb lang={lang} items={[{ label: d.title }]} />
        <div class="my-6"><DocSearch t={t} lang={lang} /></div>
        <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-extrabold gradient-text" data-reveal>{d.title}</h1>
        <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-[var(--text-secondary)] mt-4 mb-10 leading-relaxed" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="0.1">{d.desc}</p>

        <section id="manual-collection" class="mb-14 scroll-mt-28" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="0.2">
  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text)] mb-5">{d.h_manualCollection}</h2>
  <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
    HackIT does not include a dedicated report generation module. Results from each module are printed to the console during execution. To create a penetration testing report, manually collect the output from each CLI command you run.
  </p>
  <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
    Most modules support the <code class="text-[var(--accent)]">--output</code> flag to save results to a file. Use this to capture structured output that can be compiled into a report using your preferred documentation tools. Combine results from multiple modules — port scans, directory fuzzing, XSS checks, etc. — into a single document.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={`# Save scan results to a file
hackit ports scan -p 80,443 --targets target.com --output port_scan.json

# Save web fuzzer results
hackit dirfinder --url https://target.com --output dirs.json

# Save all module outputs for later compilation
hackit ssl check --url https://target.com --output ssl_results.json`} lang="bash" />
  <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--text-secondary)] mt-4 leading-relaxed">
    Collect the JSON files from each module and format them into a report manually. There are no built-in templates, branding options, or AI-generated summaries. Use tools like <strong class="text-[var(--text)]">Markdown</strong> editors or document processors to structure your findings.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="output-formats" class="mb-14 scroll-mt-28" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="0.3">
  <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text)] mb-5">{d.h_outputFormats}</h2>
  <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
    HackIT modules output results to the console in human-readable text. When the <code class="text-[var(--accent)]">--output</code> flag is provided, results are saved as <strong class="text-[var(--text)]">JSON</strong> files, making them easy to parse and integrate into automated workflows or custom reporting pipelines.
  </p>
  <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-4 leading-relaxed">
    There is no built-in PDF, HTML, or CSV export. For multi-format reporting, pipe JSON output to external tools like <code class="text-[var(--accent)]">jq</code> for transformation, or write a custom script to generate formatted documents from the saved JSON files.
  </p>
  <CodeBlock code={`# Pipe output to jq for formatting
hackit ports scan -p 80,443 --targets target.com --output - | jq '.ports[]'

# Combine multiple JSON outputs into a report
hackit web headers --url https://target.com --output headers.json
hackit ssl check --url https://target.com --output ssl.json
# Then manually combine headers.json and ssl.json into a document`}
    lang="bash" />
  <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-[var(--text-secondary)] mt-4 leading-relaxed">
    For CI/CD integration, use the <code class="text-[var(--accent)]">--output</code> flag with a file path and parse the resulting JSON in your pipeline. Each module's JSON schema is specific to that module — refer to the module's help text for output field details.
  </p>
</section>
</main>
      <DocTOC headings={headings} />
    </div>
    <DocPagination lang={lang} currentPath={Astro.url.pathname} />
  </div>
</Layout>

